G-Kross aka Baba has announced plans to hold his debut music concert in Calabar, Cross River State. This is coming after a successful launch of his debut album entitled “Son of a lion.” “It was launched online last month on several music apps such as Spotify, Boomplay, and Audiomack among others,” he said. Speaking further the young star said he remains grateful to his fans, family, and critics whose advice and criticism have made it possible for his dreams to be actualized.   TG Omori shoots over 405 music videos in five years     Emerging fashion entrepreneurs meet at Fashions Finest…     AFRIMA 2022: Entry submission portal closes on August 5   According to him, his debut album Son of a Lion was a huge success explaining that song is his story. “A true-life story that has to do with my rise from rags to riches, street to fame. this wouldn’t have been possible without the support and criticism from friends, family members as well as my amiable fans whose insatiable want for more has made it possible for a dream to be actualised.” He mentioned the likes of “Legendary king, Jonny Kageeee, Beatstar, Pat for peace, my ever loyal chief protocol officer, Vision x, among many others.” G-Kross maintained that his debut concert which comes up later this year in Calabar and will have guest appearances fun lovers and seekers can’t afford to miss. The preparation for the music concert to be held later in the year in Calabar is in top gear. He said notable national artists of high repute will be on stage with indigenous artists.